<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="58" type="differential diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="58">Differential diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="58">
Very distinct 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Ischiodon" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ischiodon" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Ischiodon</taxonomicName>
species with a darker overall coloration (Figs 3E, 5C), face yellow with a medial black vitta (Figs 3F, 5B) and terga 2-4 with two small, oblique yellow maculae not reaching the lateral margins (Fig. 5A, C). Males of 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. feae" pageId="3" pageNumber="58" rank="species" species="feae">I. feae</taxonomicName>
have fore legs with asymmetrical claws and metatrochanter without calcar.
</paragraph>
